<div id="review_246092845" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/246092845" />
    <a title="Lisa Kay" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2459470-lisa-kay"><img alt="Lisa Kay" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1534570690p2/2459470.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/246092845?book_show_action=true">Dec 12, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisa Kay" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisa Kay" href="/user/show/2459470-lisa-kay">Lisa Kay</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=m-pb-paperback">m-pb-paperback</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=reviewed-by-me">reviewed-by-me</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=authors-i">authors-i</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=m-library-sj-audio-ocd">m-library-sj-audio-ocd</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=all-time-favorites">all-time-favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=character-child-children-featured">character-child-children-featured</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=character-blonde-hero">character-blonde-hero</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=challenge-disney-princess-reading">challenge-disney-princess-reading</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=authors-a">authors-a</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2459470-lisa-kay?shelf=its-magic">its-magic</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer246092845" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3488183755836931137"><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380364794ra/716573.gif' width='100' height='100' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/>★★★★★ Wow! Adored this book! It grabbed me and wouldn’t let go. I am actually reading it for the second time. I mean <i>
  <b>in a row!</b>
</i> Amazing. IA has created a captivating world here – well three, actually: The Broken, The Weird, and The Edge – as well as characters that leap off the page and into a <i>
  <b>delicious</b>
</i> plot and back-story. I’ll admit I was confused at first; Urban Fantasy is not my strong suit. However, I have never had this kind of dilemma before: since I wanted some clarification, did</span>
  <span id="freeText3488183755836931137" style="display:none"><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380364794ra/716573.gif" width="100" height="100" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br>★★★★★ Wow! Adored this book! It grabbed me and wouldn’t let go. I am actually reading it for the second time. I mean <i>
  <b>in a row!</b>
</i> Amazing. IA has created a captivating world here – well three, actually: The Broken, The Weird, and The Edge – as well as characters that leap off the page and into a <i>
  <b>delicious</b>
</i> plot and back-story. I’ll admit I was confused at first; Urban Fantasy is not my strong suit. However, I have never had this kind of dilemma before: since I wanted some clarification, did I start over at the beginning when I was on Chapter nine and re-read, just pick and choose sections to double check, or continue on because it was getting so delicious? I started completely over and loved every minute of it – picking up nuances about these parallel fantasy worlds and characters’ quirks I loved. Now I’m reading it all over <i>
  <b>again</b>
</i> <br><br><i>White Light by Hengki Koentjoro</i><br><span>[image error]</span><br></span>
